1780
01:32:51,446 --> 01:32:55,586
Next up, Touch ID.

1781
01:32:55,583 --> 01:32:58,123
[ Applause ]

1782
01:32:58,119 --> 01:33:02,829
From the moment we
introduced Touch ID,

1783
01:33:02,824 --> 01:33:05,664
developers were excited
about the potential

1784
01:33:05,660 --> 01:33:07,430
and there's no question why,

1785
01:33:07,429 --> 01:33:10,899
Touch ID has been
extremely popular

1786
01:33:10,899 --> 01:33:12,739
and people authenticating
in their devices.

1787
01:33:12,734 --> 01:33:14,704
If you look at passcode usage

1788
01:33:14,703 --> 01:33:17,803
on iOS before Touch
ID was less than half.

1789
01:33:17,806 --> 01:33:23,176
On iPhone 5s 83 percent,
people love using Touch ID.

1790
01:33:23,178 --> 01:33:26,118
And now, third party
apps can take advantage

1791
01:33:26,114 --> 01:33:28,554
of Touch ID as well.

1792
01:33:28,550 --> 01:33:36,420
[ Applause ]

1793
01:33:36,424 --> 01:33:39,224
So Touch ID protects logins
and user data and it works

1794
01:33:39,227 --> 01:33:41,667
by unlocking Keychain items.

1795
01:33:41,663 --> 01:33:44,663
So it identifies successful
fingerprint matches

1796
01:33:44,666 --> 01:33:47,766
but it always keeps the
fingerprint data itself

1797
01:33:47,769 --> 01:33:49,569
completely protected inside

1798
01:33:49,571 --> 01:33:53,071
of the Secure Enclave
in the A7 processor.

1799
01:33:53,074 --> 01:33:55,174
The fingerprint information
is never exposed

1800
01:33:55,176 --> 01:33:58,076
to third party apps or the rest
of the system for that matter.

1801
01:33:58,079 --> 01:34:00,149
It's very secure.

1802
01:34:00,148 --> 01:34:01,278
That's Touch ID.

1803
01:34:01,282 --> 01:34:03,522
Then next, Cameras.

