01:34:38,953 --> 01:34:42,323
Now, there are a lot of great
home automation devices coming

1815
01:34:42,323 --> 01:34:44,563
on the market these days and
they have companion apps,

1816
01:34:44,559 --> 01:34:48,929
things like lights and
door locks, webcams,

1817
01:34:48,930 --> 01:34:52,400
garage doors, and thermostats.

1818
01:34:52,400 --> 01:34:55,070
But, you know, each of them
have their own application

1819
01:34:55,069 --> 01:34:59,009
and they end up defining
their own network protocol,

1820
01:34:59,007 --> 01:35:01,477
their own security mechanisms.

1821
01:35:01,476 --> 01:35:05,116
Well, we thought we could bring
some rationality to the space.

1822
01:35:05,113 --> 01:35:07,813
We started working
with the leaders

1823
01:35:07,816 --> 01:35:10,286
in home automation devices.

1824
01:35:10,285 --> 01:35:15,125
And we've come up with HomeKit
with a common network protocol

1825
01:35:15,123 --> 01:35:17,423
that has secure pairing
to ensure

1826
01:35:17,425 --> 01:35:20,765
that only your iPhone
can open your garage door

1827
01:35:20,762 --> 01:35:22,632
or unlock your door.

1828
01:35:22,630 --> 01:35:25,770
And in addition to being able
to control individual devices

1829
01:35:25,767 --> 01:35:29,507
in your home, with HomeKit you
can group devices and changes

1830
01:35:29,504 --> 01:35:33,144
in the scenes and then with
Siri integration you can say

1831
01:35:33,141 --> 01:35:35,711
something like, "Get ready
for bed," and be assured

1832
01:35:35,710 --> 01:35:38,380
that your garage door is
closed, your door is locked,

1833
01:35:38,379 --> 01:35:39,679
the thermostat is lower,

1834
01:35:39,681 --> 01:35:43,551
and your lights are
dimmed, that's HomeKit.

1835
01:35:43,551 --> 01:35:51,591
[ Applause ]

1836
01:35:51,593 --> 01:35:53,933
Next, CloudKit.

1837
01:35:53,928 --> 01:35:55,828
So today, if you're a developer

1838
01:35:55,830 --> 01:35:57,530
and you're writing
an application

1839
01:35:57,532 --> 01:36:00,632
and it needs a web component,
well, you end up really having

1840
01:36:00,635 --> 01:36:02,635
to write two apps in one.

1841
01:36:02,637 --> 01:36:05,507
In addition to the writing in
the client side using Xcode

1842
01:36:05,506 --> 01:36:06,846
and our frameworks, you have

1843
01:36:06,841 --> 01:36:08,211
to write the server
side of the app.

1844
01:36:08,209 --> 01:36:11,809
You have to write server side
app logic, you have to deal

1845
01:36:11,813 --> 01:36:14,653
with authentication, asset
