1846
01:36:14,649 --> 01:36:17,019
search, even push
notifications and then you got

1847
01:36:17,018 --> 01:36:19,288
to pay somebody to host it all.

1848
01:36:19,287 --> 01:36:23,087
Well, now, with CloudKit,
CloudKit takes

1849
01:36:23,091 --> 01:36:25,761
over the cloud part
and provide you

1850
01:36:25,760 --> 01:36:28,360
with a client side
programming model

1851
01:36:28,363 --> 01:36:32,563
that lets you access iCloud
authentication storage,

1852
01:36:32,567 --> 01:36:34,537
search and more.

1853
01:36:34,535 --> 01:36:36,875
And when it comes to paying,

1854
01:36:36,871 --> 01:36:45,751
CloudKit is effectively
free, with limits.

1855
01:36:45,747 --> 01:36:49,647
So, CloudKit scales the
data allocated to your app

1856
01:36:49,651 --> 01:36:53,291
and bandwidth based on the
number of users using your app.

1857
01:36:53,288 --> 01:36:56,958
And this goes all the way up
to granting you free a petabyte

1858
01:36:56,958 --> 01:36:59,428
of assets, 10 terabytes
of database

1859
01:36:59,427 --> 01:37:02,927
and all the bandwidth you
can constructively use.

1860
01:37:02,931 --> 01:37:05,501
That is CloudKit.

